data.title: Philadelphia Sixers Roster
data.meta_description: Philadelphia Sixers scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Samuel Dalembert was selected as the #26 pick in the First Round of the 2001 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Samuel Dalembert signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 6, 2001. Samuel Dalembert re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 2, 2005.

Jrue Holiday was selected as the #17 pick in the First Round of the 2009 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Jrue Holiday signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 20, 2009.

Andre Iguodala was selected as the #9 pick in the First Round of the 2004 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Andre Iguodala signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 2, 2004. Andre Iguodala re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 18, 2008.

Marreese Speights was selected as the #16 pick in the First Round of the 2008 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Marreese Speights signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 10, 2008.

Lou Williams was selected as the #15 pick in the Second Round of the 2005 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Lou Williams signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 18, 2005. Lou Williams re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 4, 2008.

Thaddeus Young was selected as the #12 pick in the First Round of the 2007 NBA Draft by the Philadelphia Sixers. Thaddeus Young signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 10, 2007.

Draft Rights to Willie Green, the #12 pick in the Second Round of the 2003 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Philadelphia Sixers from the Seattle SuperSonics on June 26, 2003. Willie Green signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on August 8, 2003. Willie Green re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Philadelphia Sixers on March 23, 2006. Willie Green re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 12, 2006.

Draft Rights to Jason Smith, the #20 pick in the First Round of the 2007 NBA Draft, were acquired by the Philadelphia Sixers from the Miami Heat on June 28, 2007. Jason Smith signed a multi-year contract with the Philadelphia Sixers on July 10, 2007.
